==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ineloquent
<hw>In*e"lo*quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ineloquens</ets>: cf. F. <ets>in⟦eacute⟧loquent</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Eloquent</er>.]</ety> <def>Not eloquent; not
fluent, graceful, or moving; not persuasive; <as>as, <ex>ineloquent</ex>
language</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor are thy lips ungraceful, sire of men,⟦br⟧
Nor tongue <qex>ineloquent</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ineloquently</ent>⟦br⟧
